  "root_text": {
    "an4.40:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4.40 ",
    "an4.40:0.2": "4. Cakkavagga ",
    "an4.40:0.3": "Udāyīsutta ",
    "an4.40:1.1": "Atha kho udāyī brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā …pe… ekamantaṁ nisinno kho udāyī brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "an4.40:1.2": "“bhavampi no gotamo yaññaṁ vaṇṇetī”ti? ",
    "an4.40:1.3": "“Na kho ahaṁ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṁ yaññaṁ vaṇṇemi; ",
    "an4.40:1.4": "na panāhaṁ, brāhmaṇa, sabbaṁ yaññaṁ na vaṇṇemi. ",
    "an4.40:1.5": "Yathārūpe kho, brāhmaṇa, yaññe gāvo haññanti, ajeḷakā haññanti, kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, vividhā pāṇā saṅghātaṁ āpajjanti; ",
    "an4.40:1.6": "evarūpaṁ kho ahaṁ, brāhmaṇa, sārambhaṁ yaññaṁ na vaṇṇemi. ",
    "an4.40:1.7": "Taṁ kissa hetu? ",
    "an4.40:1.8": "Evarūpañhi, brāhmaṇa, sārambhaṁ yaññaṁ na upasaṅkamanti arahanto vā arahattamaggaṁ vā samāpannā. ",
    "an4.40:2.1": "Yathārūpe ca kho, brāhmaṇa, yaññe neva gāvo haññanti, na ajeḷakā haññanti, na kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, na vividhā pāṇā saṅghātaṁ āpajjanti; ",
    "an4.40:2.2": "evarūpaṁ kho ahaṁ, brāhmaṇa, nirārambhaṁ yaññaṁ vaṇṇemi, yadidaṁ niccadānaṁ anukulayaññaṁ. ",
    "an4.40:2.3": "Taṁ kissa hetu? ",
    "an4.40:2.4": "Evarūpañhi, brāhmaṇa, nirārambhaṁ yaññaṁ upasaṅkamanti arahanto vā arahattamaggaṁ vā samāpannāti. ",
    "an4.40:3.1": "Abhisaṅkhataṁ nirārambhaṁ, ",
    "an4.40:3.2": "yaññaṁ kālena kappiyaṁ; ",
    "an4.40:3.3": "Tādisaṁ upasaṁyanti, ",
    "an4.40:3.4": "saññatā brahmacārayo. ",
    "an4.40:4.1": "Vivaṭacchadā ye loke, ",
    "an4.40:4.2": "vītivattā kulaṁ gatiṁ; ",
    "an4.40:4.3": "Yaññametaṁ pasaṁsanti, ",
    "an4.40:4.4": "buddhā yaññassa kovidā. ",
    "an4.40:5.1": "Yaññe vā yadi vā saddhe, ",
    "an4.40:5.2": "habyaṁ katvā yathārahaṁ; ",
    "an4.40:5.3": "Pasannacitto yajati, ",
    "an4.40:5.4": "sukhette brahmacārisu. ",
    "an4.40:6.1": "Suhutaṁ suyiṭṭhaṁ suppattaṁ, ",
    "an4.40:6.2": "Dakkhiṇeyyesu yaṁ kataṁ; ",
    "an4.40:6.3": "Yañño ca vipulo hoti, ",
    "an4.40:6.4": "Pasīdanti ca devatā. ",
    "an4.40:7.1": "Evaṁ yajitvā medhāvī, ",
    "an4.40:7.2": "saddho muttena cetasā; ",
    "an4.40:7.3": "Abyābajjhaṁ sukhaṁ lokaṁ, ",
    "an4.40:7.4": "paṇḍito upapajjatī”ti. ",
    "an4.40:7.5": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "an4.40:7.6": "Cakkavaggo catuttho. ",
    "an4.40:8.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "an4.40:8.1": "Cakko saṅgaho sīho, ",
    "an4.40:8.2": "Pasādo vassakārena pañcamaṁ; ",
    "an4.40:8.3": "Doṇo aparihāniyo patilīno, ",
    "an4.40:8.4": "Ujjayo udāyinā te dasāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an4.40:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 4.40 ",
    "an4.40:0.2": "4. Situations ",
    "an4.40:0.3": "With Udāyī ",
    "an4.40:1.1": "Then Udāyī the brahmin went up to the Buddha, … and asked him, ",
    "an4.40:1.2": "“Does the worthy Gotama praise sacrifice?” ",
    "an4.40:1.3": "“Brahmin, I don’t praise all sacrifices. ",
    "an4.40:1.4": "Nor do I criticize all sacrifices. … ",
    "an4.40:1.5": "Take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and various kinds of animals are slaughtered. ",
    "an4.40:1.6": "I don’t praise that kind of violent sacrifice. ",
    "an4.40:1.7": "",
    "an4.40:1.8": "",
    "an4.40:2.1": "But take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and various kinds of animals are not slaughtered. ",
    "an4.40:2.2": "I do praise that kind of non-violent sacrifice; for example, a regular gift as an propitious sacrifice. ",
    "an4.40:2.3": "",
    "an4.40:2.4": "",
    "an4.40:3.1": "The kind of sacrifice that’s allowable and timely, ",
    "an4.40:3.2": "well prepared and non-violent, ",
    "an4.40:3.3": "is attended by ",
    "an4.40:3.4": "disciplined spiritual practitioners. ",
    "an4.40:4.1": "The Buddhas—<j>who have drawn back the veil from the world, ",
    "an4.40:4.2": "passing beyond time and rebirth—",
    "an4.40:4.3": "praise this sacrifice, ",
    "an4.40:4.4": "as they are expert in sacrifice. ",
    "an4.40:5.1": "When you’ve prepared a suitable offering, ",
    "an4.40:5.2": "whether as sacrifice or for ancestors, ",
    "an4.40:5.3": "sacrifice it with confident heart, ",
    "an4.40:5.4": "in the fertile field of spiritual practitioners. ",
    "an4.40:6.1": "When it’s well-gotten, well-offered, <j>and well-sacrificed, ",
    "an4.40:6.2": "to those worthy of a religious donation, ",
    "an4.40:6.3": "a sacrifice is truly abundant, ",
    "an4.40:6.4": "and even the deities are pleased. ",
    "an4.40:7.1": "When an intelligent, faithful person, ",
    "an4.40:7.2": "sacrifices like this, with a mind of letting go, ",
    "an4.40:7.3": "that astute one is reborn ",
    "an4.40:7.4": "in a happy, pleasing world.” ",
    "an4.40:7.5": "",
    "an4.40:7.6": "",
    "an4.40:8.1": "",
    "an4.40:8.2": "",
    "an4.40:8.3": ""
  },
